Lunarpine moved slowly across the ground so he wouldn't give his 
position away. he activated his claws, with the damage to his left 
arm his claws were nearly useless. He knew where he dropped his gun 
but didn't dare try for it, that was probably the first thing his 
opponent would try to avoid.

His sense of smell was the main advantage that he had, he knew the 
opponent was closeing fast and had a powerful weapon. But if it was a 
typical predacon it would try for an up close and personal kill. Just 
so it could gloat.
